This template is used to display information on a [[star system]] consisting of 1 star.  The template should be used as shown below.  Unused arguments may be omitted.

There are two possibilities for displaying the right ascension and declination.
# Formatting is done by the template.  Use <tt>ra_h</tt>, <tt>ra_m</tt>, <tt>ra_s</tt>, <tt>dec_d</tt>, <tt>dec_m</tt>, and <tt>dec_s</tt>.
# Formatting is done by the editor.  Use <tt>ra</tt> or <tt>ra_1</tt> for the first line of right ascension and <tt>dec</tt> or <tt>dec_1</tt> for the first line of declination.  If a second line is desired, use <tt>ra_2</tt> for the second line of right ascension, and <tt>dec_2</tt> for the second line of declination. Use of the {{tl|RA}} template is recommended for formatting the right ascension, and the {{tl|DEC}} template for formatting the declination. 

If the argument <tt>parallax</tt> is provided and <tt>dist_ly</tt> and <tt>dist_pc</tt> are omitted, the distances will be calculated automatically from the parallax (and the parallax error <tt>p_error</tt>, if provided.)

